I wish I would have slowed down a little more when I was full tilt traveling the world, you have no idea how fast it can all get taken away from you. Enjoy all the little things because at the end of the you’ll realize they were the big things. Extremely grateful for the incredible life BMX gave me and all the countries I got to visit, have endless great memories that seem fake to a small kid growing up in Nova Scotia, where everything looked out of reach.  Blessed 🙏🙌🏼. @teamtoyota @ethika @ryderbmx  @odi_bmx  #bmx #ethika #odi #odigrips  #withyoueverywhere #2011

180 berm I built when I was 12.  I loved dirt jumping so much. I would wake up at 6am on summer break to build something new for me and my friends to ride after they got home from racking blueberries to buy new school clothes.  I built a 6 pack to a 180 berm then you would sprint back to another jump  copying an old Gravity games course I seen on TV.  Can’t wait to be back to the grind. Slowly but surely.
Never a dull moment hanging out with @texasmwade  we always put safely first 😝 RedBull project in Wales

3 years ago today, with a pressure guage in my skull my parents were told it could go either way. This was the start of a 15 day coma. By the grace of god I’m still here. Numerous broken bones, a stroke and  multiple surgeries and I was put back together
IT, wasn’t my time. Extremely blessed 🙏🙏🙏❤️‍🩹
Took two hours to cut me out just as I flat lined for a second. Again so blessed to still be here. My works not done here yet 🙏🙏🙏
Went from a short box to a short cab. beyond lucky 🍀.

Three years and 9 days ago this was almost my tomb stone. Which I crashed inyo because of a seizure while I was driving brought on by a previous head injury. There was no way of knowing when it was going to happen. So to the people who thought it was an attempt to take my own life 🖕🏼🖕🏼🖕🏼🖕🏼🖕🏼 p  I have the rest of my life# to enjoy ever last day I have on this beautiful earth.

I can’t wait to get back to Ontario and meet the first responders on my accident and thank DR Henry who put my right leg back together in 3-4 surgeries 5 plates and 16 screws 🙏. Blessed to be able to walk. Still waiting to get better rehab.  Timing is key hopefully this time next year I’ll be able to rolling on two wheels.  Still a long road ahead of me
